{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"44981eeb-34c8-4570-b5e3-8de0e1d5b519","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is an executable. `dotnet run` launches that executable directly, enabling the hot reload loop — it watches for file changes and re-runs tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` uses the traditional VSTest adapter path and **does not** support hot reload.\n\nSo run:\n\n```bash\nDOTNET_WATCH_RESTART=true dotnet watch run\n```\n\nor simply:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run\n```\n\nYour project already has `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled and the hot reload package referenced, so you're all set.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"10014d1f-8820-4fad-8377-c2fad6c138b3","outputTokens":167,"requestId":"9832:254503:29C4DE:36CF62:69FFE28D"},"id":"318e9bb6-5617-4bd9-a54e-a27f1f2ff751","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:42:43.268Z","parentId":"17e2a602-a469-40f7-bbf4-ee8eed445935"}
